This paper deals with improving recommendation quality and user engagement in the context of Amazon Music. This falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to achieve this goal, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.CY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of relevance scores, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the diversification of recommendations, which is a common theme in social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
